1
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:52,240
Caibao,

2
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:54,420
have you finished your proposal?

3
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:56,160
N-no.

4
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:57,440
I... I'm too tired.

5
00:01:57,440 --> 00:01:59,280
I'm just stretching a bit.

6
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:02,000
I'll get to it right away.

7
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:17,060
Caibao.

8
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:26,440
Wei,

9
00:02:26,720 --> 00:02:27,579
let me help you.

10
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:30,360
Just say what you want to say.

11
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:31,520
Wei,

12
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,680
lately, our team's

13
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:35,160
atmosphere has been too oppressive

14
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:36,160
and suffocating.

15
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:38,360
My weak and helpless heart

16
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:39,880
really can't take it.

17
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:43,360
Ask yourself,

18
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:45,090
is my proposal really that bad?

19
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,160
Not really.

20
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:49,200
Then do you think his proposal is better than mine?

21
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:50,120
It actually is.

22
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:52,480
Wei,

23
00:02:52,760 --> 00:02:53,760
to be honest,

24
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:54,920
we finally managed

25
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:56,450
to get into flight control.

26
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:57,800
We got a task as soon as we came in,

27
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:00,320
and there are so many eyes on us now.

28
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:03,000
We have to deliver on this, don't we?

29
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,000
I know.

30
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:04,760
I...

31
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:05,280
Wei,

32
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:06,600
I know you want to do better,

33
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:08,080
but we also have to act according to our capabilities, right?

34
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:10,120
Yes, Qi's attitude is very negative,

35
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,480
but he has a point.

36
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:14,120
Even the best ideas have to be put into practice.

37
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:15,180
Taking a step back,

38
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:18,040
no matter whose proposal we use in the end,

39
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:19,960
shouldn't we unite to do it well?

40
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:21,440
You came from Mr. Zhao's side.

41
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:22,900
If you go back in disgrace,

42
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:24,000
how embarrassing would that be?

43
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,120
Can you let me finish first?

44
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:28,200
Okay, you speak.

45
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:29,680
I just think...

46
00:03:31,760 --> 00:03:32,880
Where was I?

47
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:34,579
It doesn't matter.

48
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,130
I know what you mean.

49
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:38,250
I won't argue with him anymore.

50
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:40,520
I also know I have many shortcomings.

51
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:41,960
Just like everyone else,

52
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:44,560
I hope the flight simulation will be a success.

53
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:46,120
I know what's important.

54
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:48,579
I will cooperate with the team. Don't worry.

55
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:50,120
That's right.

56
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:51,650
That's my good brother Wei.

57
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:53,880
Just like that, your perspective broadens.

58
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:55,210
Shadow Fiend Vanguard.

59
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:57,600
Jia,

60
00:03:58,640 --> 00:03:59,480
I actually...

61
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:01,410
Have you finished your proposals?

62
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:02,400
Not yet.

63
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:05,120
Then why are you chatting? Hurry up and get to work.

64
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:06,440
Caibao, you too.

65
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:08,800
Go. Go. Go.

66
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:40,040
Son.

67
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:43,880
Uncle, Aunt.

68
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:46,280
Hello.

69
00:05:46,280 --> 00:05:47,280
Please come in.

70
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:48,280
Qi,

71
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:50,040
Mom and Dad came to see you.

72
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,180
Is this your roommate?

73
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:55,840
Auntie, I'm Wu Wei.

74
00:05:56,159 --> 00:05:57,200
From the Hangda family courtyard.

75
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:59,930
It's been too long, you probably don't remember.

76
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:02,800
Wu Wei, I remember.

77
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:05,620
You ate at our house when you were little.

78
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:07,880
Then you moved, right?

79
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:08,560
Yes.

80
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:11,360
That's wonderful. You've both grown so much.

81
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:13,640
You were good friends when you were little.

82
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:15,280
Now you are roommates.

83
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:16,440
It must be fate.

84
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,520
Auntie, I'll leave you two to talk.

85
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:19,040
All right.

86
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:19,840
You go ahead.

87
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:24,200
You haven't been home for so long.

88
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:26,440
Mom and Dad had to come see you.

89
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,720
Are you used to the dorm?

90
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:31,200
Do you have to work overtime?

91
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:32,880
How's the food in the cafeteria?

92
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:34,440
Tell me all about it.

93
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:37,159
Son, do you have any plans?

94
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,080
What plans?

95
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,920
For the future, of course.

96
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:44,600
Listen to me.

97
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:47,840
Career planning is crucial.

98
00:06:48,159 --> 00:06:50,020
Are you going to be a professional

99
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:52,280
or take the administrative route?

100
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:54,560
Knowing when and how to do it

101
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:55,640
is very important.

102
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,159
I'm telling you, it's like playing chess.

103
00:06:58,159 --> 00:07:00,600
You have to think three steps ahead.

104
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:04,120
I've looked into it for you.

105
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:06,160
In the aerospace system,

106
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:08,200
the youngest chief designer

107
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:10,080
was appointed at the age of 30.

108
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:12,240
You're 25 this year

109
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:13,570
and you don't have a PhD.

110
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:15,640
So you have to hurry.

111
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:17,920
No matter what, in your first year,

112
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:20,600
you have to get the professional title.

113
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:22,260
I haven't thought about that.

114
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:24,760
How can you not, son?

115
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:29,020
He who gives no thought to the future is sure to be beset by worries at hand.

116
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,080
I'm telling you.

117
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,360
You're my son.

118
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:34,920
I will support whatever you do.

119
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:36,560
But how you will develop in the future,

120
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:38,280
you have to know what you want.

121
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:41,800
You have to set a big goal now.

122
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:45,000
Then you can move forward step by step

123
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,159
and climb up.

124
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:50,120
You can't do stupid things.

125
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:52,320
You can't just immerse yourself in tasks all day

126
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:53,520
and make no progress.

127
00:07:54,320 --> 00:07:57,159
All those who can enter the aerospace system

128
00:07:57,159 --> 00:07:58,480
and flight control

129
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:00,960
are one in a million.

130
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:02,040
Once you enter the unit,

131
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:03,880
everyone is on the same starting line.

132
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:05,360
But what about five years later?

133
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,720
Ten years later?

134
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:08,600
How many can become chief designers?

135
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:10,840
How many can become academicians?

136
00:08:10,840 --> 00:08:12,920
The gap will be huge.

137
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:15,040
Most people

138
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:18,000
work hard their whole lives

139
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:20,320
and just end up as a subordinate.

140
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:21,520
Mom.

141
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:25,320
Do you remember the Math Olympiad when I was little?

142
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:27,050
I got second place nationwide.

143
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:29,760
You threw away my medal

144
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,160
and hit me.

145
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:34,000
You promised me before the competition

146
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,600
that after the award ceremony,

147
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:37,760
we'd go to the Rocket Competition to find Wu Wei.

148
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:39,289
But you broke your promise.

149
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:40,640
You told me that day

150
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:44,920
that nothing mattered but being the champion.

151
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:47,800
I still remember it.

152
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:51,040
Whether it's rockets or the Math Olympiad,

153
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:53,000
they are both interesting to me.

154
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:54,240
But I just don't understand

155
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:55,840
why I have to be the champion.

156
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:58,200
What's the point of being the champion?

157
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,200
I've understood since then.

158
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:05,200
Everything in this world

159
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:06,930
doesn't have to be meaningful,

160
00:09:07,160 --> 00:09:08,690
but it must be interesting.

161
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:11,600
But right now,

162
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:14,660
I don't know the purpose of my existence.

163
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:16,240
Why do I...

164
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:18,100
have to do something meaningful?

165
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:26,440
Wu Wei.

166
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:30,800
What took you so long?

167
00:09:32,680 --> 00:09:33,880
You chickened out.

168
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:36,240
We agreed to enter the competition and win together.

169
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:37,480
What took you so long?

170
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:40,620
Is the championship that important?

171
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:42,280
Only winning is meaningful.

172
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:45,720
What's more important, winning or friends?

173
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:47,520
The championship is important.

174
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:56,800
How can you

175
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,800
think like that?

176
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:01,200
Auntie,

177
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:03,570
I don't think you're right.

178
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,280
My mom was just a regular worker who devoted her life

179
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:06,810
to the aerospace industry.

180
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:08,600
I chose aerospace as a career,

181
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,040
never for fame and fortune,

182
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:11,000
but for passion.

183
00:10:11,880 --> 00:10:13,010
This passion of mine

184
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:14,520
may be because of my parents,

185
00:10:14,520 --> 00:10:17,320
because of friends, because of childhood dreams,

186
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:20,320
but it's definitely not for titles, fame, or fortune.

187
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:21,160
Xiao Wu,

188
00:10:21,560 --> 00:10:23,840
you're still young, you don't understand these things.

189
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:25,040
Auntie has been through this.

190
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:27,170
I'm doing all this for Ziqi's own good.

191
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:27,960
Auntie,

192
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:30,320
everyone in the space city

193
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:31,780
moves forward step by step

194
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:34,320
for their ideals and driven by their passion.

195
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:36,760
Many things cannot be measured by utility.

196
00:10:37,040 --> 00:10:40,880
Passion itself is the meaning of passion.

197
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:43,480
Xiao Wu,

198
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:45,160
I think you misunderstood

199
00:10:45,160 --> 00:10:46,360
what I meant.

200
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:48,840
Then since it's a passion,

201
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:50,970
you need success even more.

202
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:52,080
Right?

203
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:53,000
Auntie...

204
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:53,800
Stop talking.

205
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:00,240
Sorry, Auntie.

206
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,480
You guys keep talking.

207
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:02,560
Take care, Xiao Wu.

208
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:07,840
Mom, Dad,

209
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:10,020
it's getting late.

210
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:11,960
We still have work tomorrow.

211
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,620
Why don't you head back first?

212
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:19,440
Okay.

213
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:22,010
I won't be an eyesore here anymore.

214
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:24,600
I'll leave all these materials here for you.

215
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:27,000
Think about it when you have some free time.

216
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:30,360
The food I brought you,

217
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:32,000
your dad put it all in the fridge.

218
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:32,800
Remember,

219
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:35,560
you must eat eggs and drink milk in the morning.

220
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:38,080
And you must come home on weekends.

221
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:39,920
We asked Mr. Qin,

222
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:42,220
you're allowed to go out on weekends.

223
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:44,160
Come home and visit when you are free.

224
00:11:44,160 --> 00:11:44,960
Come home.

225
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:47,040
Mr. Chen, wait for me.

226
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:47,960
Wait for me.

227
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:01,080
I chose aerospace as my career,

228
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,340
not for fame or wealth,

229
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:03,560
but for love.

230
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:06,290
This passion of mine

231
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:08,240
might be because of my parents,

232
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:10,480
my friends, or a childhood dream,

233
00:12:11,040 --> 00:12:13,170
but definitely not for titles or fame.

234
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,360
Everyone in the Aerospace City

235
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:24,760
is here for their ideals.

236
00:12:25,040 --> 00:12:27,360
Moving forward step by step with passion.

237
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:29,760
Many things can't be measured by utility.

238
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,480
Passion itself

239
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:34,360
is the meaning of passion.

240
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:56,650
The appointment is at nine, right?

241
00:12:58,120 --> 00:12:58,760
Nan,

242
00:12:59,800 --> 00:13:02,120
Do you think when they come with the plans later,

243
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:03,120
and we grade them,

244
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:05,160
they won't fight again, will they?

245
00:13:05,160 --> 00:13:07,320
We've tried everything we could.

246
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:09,440
The rest is up to them.

247
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:11,530
No matter how they fight today,

248
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:13,240
we have to choose a plan today.

249
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:14,700
We can't delay it anymore.

250
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:16,360
You know,

251
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:17,840
if I also had top-tier skills,

252
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:18,970
that would be great.

253
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:20,600
If only I could have proposed a

254
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:22,040
more mature plan back then,

255
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:23,300
to balance things out,

256
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:24,960
they wouldn't be fighting.

257
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:26,760
All right, I don't blame you.

258
00:13:29,640 --> 00:13:31,840
Let's not wait for them and start first.

259
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:52,880
You go first.

260
00:13:58,240 --> 00:14:00,100
Both of you speak at the same time.

261
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:09,620
I thought about it last night.

262
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:11,530
Let's use your plan.

263
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:21,680
I also researched it yesterday.

264
00:14:22,160 --> 00:14:24,280
My plan may indeed not be secure enough.

265
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:27,200
There are some steps I'm not confident about doing well.

266
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,320
All things considered,

267
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:30,320
Ying Ziqi's might be more reliable.

268
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:33,840
Are you sure you want to use my plan?

269
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:34,700
Don't force it.

270
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:37,460
I'm not forcing it.

271
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:39,120
Time is running out.

272
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:40,520
There's no need to argue anymore.

273
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:41,780
But if we use your plan,

274
00:14:42,520 --> 00:14:44,600
we need to fully prepare all contingencies

275
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:46,160
to ensure the mission's success.

276
00:14:46,160 --> 00:14:48,080
Since the pro has spoken,

277
00:14:48,560 --> 00:14:49,960
let's just do it.

278
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:52,040
If Team Muxing is going to win, we win together.

279
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:53,040
If we lose, we lose together.

280
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:54,040
Let's get to work.

281
00:16:00,920 --> 00:16:02,000
Muxing Team,

282
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:03,280
come on!

283
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:13,120
Control 1 reporting.

284
00:16:13,120 --> 00:16:15,000
Longzhou 1 and Longgong 2

285
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,600
rendezvous and docking completed.

286
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:19,040
Both spacecraft attitudes and data are normal.

287
00:16:19,040 --> 00:16:22,360
The first rendezvous and docking simulation flight control is finished.

288
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:25,220
Preparing for radial rendezvous and docking test.

289
00:16:27,880 --> 00:16:28,760
It's our turn.

290
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:35,760
Control 3, please take over the command for the second docking test.

291
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:41,960
Leaders, experts,

292
00:16:42,360 --> 00:16:43,320
we will now conduct

293
00:16:43,320 --> 00:16:46,040
Muxing team's simulated flight control for rendezvous and docking.

294
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:46,920
Attention, all stations.

295
00:16:46,920 --> 00:16:49,760
Perform the final check before simulated rendezvous and docking.

296
00:16:49,760 --> 00:16:50,620
Control 2 copy.

297
00:16:50,760 --> 00:16:52,040
The following parking point has been confirmed.

298
00:16:52,040 --> 00:16:52,800
Control 5 copy.

299
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:54,560
The parking point data has been uploaded.

300
00:16:54,560 --> 00:16:55,480
Control 4 copy.

301
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:57,010
Data monitoring is normal.

302
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,920
Unlike forward rendezvous and docking,

303
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:03,040
this radial docking

304
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:05,000
uses a bottom-up approach,

305
00:17:05,240 --> 00:17:06,640
which is more difficult.

306
00:17:07,040 --> 00:17:08,119
Control 4, attention.

307
00:17:08,119 --> 00:17:10,250
Report at the relative distance node.

308
00:17:12,079 --> 00:17:12,960
Control 4 reporting.

309
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:14,440
Longzhou-1 attitude is normal.

310
00:17:14,440 --> 00:17:16,240
Longgong-2 attitude is normal.

311
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:18,200
The relative distance between the two

312
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:20,000
is 411.382 meters.

313
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:22,000
Relative speed is 0.45 meters per second.

314
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:23,930
Commencing radial pulse docking.

315
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:25,640
Control 5, copy.

316
00:17:25,640 --> 00:17:27,770
Switching to the carrier camera feed.

317
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:29,690
Control 2, copy.

318
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:31,400
Docking mechanism getting ready.

319
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:32,360
Control 4 reporting.

320
00:17:32,360 --> 00:17:35,220
Entering scheduled rendezvous and docking orbit.

321
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:38,440
Control 4 reporting.

322
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:40,200
Dragon Boat 1 attitude is normal.

323
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:41,720
Dragon Palace 2 attitude is normal.

324
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:44,360
Relative distance between the two spacecraft is 350 meters.

325
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:45,240
250 meters.

326
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:47,370
Preparing for automatic docking.

327
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:49,160
Control 3, copy that.

328
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:54,640
Control 4 reporting.

329
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:56,480
The two spacecraft are 200 meters apart.

330
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:58,140
Relative attitude is normal.

331
00:18:01,920 --> 00:18:03,520
The distance between the two crafts is 150 meters.

332
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:04,580
The relative speed

333
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:07,690
hasn't slowed down.

334
00:18:08,480 --> 00:18:10,680
Why is the relative speed still so fast?

335
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:11,680
Quick, get the contingency manual

336
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:12,810
and find a solution.

337
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:15,040
Here, here.

338
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:16,080
The manual.

339
00:18:20,360 --> 00:18:21,400
Relative speed.

340
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:22,320
Look here.

341
00:18:22,320 --> 00:18:23,650
The relative velocity.

342
00:18:23,760 --> 00:18:24,600
Here.

343
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:26,280
In protocol 3112,

344
00:18:26,280 --> 00:18:29,760
there is a command to adjust the relative velocity of the modules.

345
00:18:29,760 --> 00:18:31,360
Relative velocity data is abnormal.

346
00:18:31,360 --> 00:18:33,290
Control 3 requests protocol 3112.

347
00:18:34,920 --> 00:18:35,720
Control 1 copies.

348
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:37,400
Approved to proceed with the protocol.

349
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:38,880
Control 3 requests manual docking.

350
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:40,000
Manual docking approved.

351
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:40,800
Attention, Control 4.

352
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:41,920
Execute protocol 3112.

353
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:42,760
Control 4 copies.

354
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:44,760
Control 4 executing protocol 3112.

355
00:18:45,160 --> 00:18:46,400
Protocol 3112.

356
00:18:46,760 --> 00:18:47,820
Control 4 reports.

357
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:50,640
Relative distance between modules is 100 meters.

358
00:18:50,920 --> 00:18:51,780
Eighty meters.

359
00:18:53,120 --> 00:18:53,920
Sixty meters.

360
00:18:55,120 --> 00:18:55,920
Forty meters.

361
00:18:58,200 --> 00:18:59,060
Twenty meters.

362
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:33,800
Muxing Team's

363
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:36,620
simulated flight control failed this time.

364
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:43,320
Let's carefully troubleshoot

365
00:19:43,320 --> 00:19:44,320
every step.

366
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:50,730
Let's make a thorough summary.

367
00:19:56,280 --> 00:19:57,340
Back to square one.

368
00:20:00,360 --> 00:20:03,160
The satellite blew up, and Lao Qin will blow up too.

369
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:13,440
I remember my first simulated mission

370
00:21:14,360 --> 00:21:16,480
was a launch and orbit simulation.

371
00:21:18,960 --> 00:21:21,640
It was winter in Jiuquan.

372
00:21:22,280 --> 00:21:24,920
The weather was terrible back then. It was freezing.

373
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:26,920
It was so cold that no matter what food we had,

374
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:29,720
it would get cold as soon as it was brought indoors.

375
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:33,600
There was a colleague in the thermal control team.

376
00:21:34,120 --> 00:21:36,650
I still remember him very clearly to this day.

377
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:38,640
He was about your age,

378
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:40,200
maybe 27 or 28.

379
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:42,640
He was from Jiangnan.

380
00:21:42,960 --> 00:21:45,280
This guy was extremely skilled

381
00:21:45,600 --> 00:21:47,440
and especially loved to delve into research.

382
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:49,000
But because he was a southerner,

383
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:51,840
he really couldn't stand the cold of the Northwest.

384
00:21:51,840 --> 00:21:53,570
He would just curl up like this.

385
00:21:54,400 --> 00:21:56,880
That day, I don't know what he ate,

386
00:21:57,640 --> 00:21:59,000
but he got an upset stomach.

387
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:01,260
He was tossing and rolling around in bed.

388
00:22:02,520 --> 00:22:05,360
But even so, he persevered

389
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:06,850
and completed the task.

390
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:09,520
He said he had to hold on

391
00:22:09,520 --> 00:22:11,180
because it was his first time.

392
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:14,200
After it was over,

393
00:22:14,960 --> 00:22:17,440
there was a heavy snowstorm outside.

394
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:19,520
He grabbed the radio and ran out.

395
00:22:19,520 --> 00:22:22,640
He was jumping, singing, and rolling in the snow.

396
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:30,720
And then, he never got up again.

397
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:41,600
I think if he had lived to this day,

398
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:42,840
some of you

399
00:22:43,720 --> 00:22:45,360
might be his students.

400
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:54,700
He was young back then.

401
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:56,920
He also had a space dream.

402
00:22:57,760 --> 00:22:58,960
But his first time

403
00:23:00,040 --> 00:23:03,400
came to an abrupt end along with his life.

404
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:10,500
And what about you?

405
00:23:12,280 --> 00:23:14,920
Your dreams have just begun.

406
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:21,760
I want you

407
00:23:22,720 --> 00:23:24,240
to remember this moment.

408
00:23:24,240 --> 00:23:26,760
Right now, the feeling of this very moment.

409
00:23:33,520 --> 00:23:34,250
Remember it.

410
00:23:36,040 --> 00:23:38,640
It will stay with you for the rest of your lives.

411
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:09,240
Mr. Qin.

412
00:24:09,560 --> 00:24:11,360
Mr. Qin, can I say a few words?

413
00:24:12,040 --> 00:24:13,480
You're out of breath from running.

414
00:24:13,480 --> 00:24:14,010
Go ahead.

415
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:17,200
The failure of the newcomers' flight simulation this time

416
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:18,720
is completely my responsibility.

417
00:24:18,720 --> 00:24:20,120
I didn't guide them well.

418
00:24:20,360 --> 00:24:22,720
Actually, I've seen their plan.

419
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:24,760
It already showed signs of success.

420
00:24:24,760 --> 00:24:26,600
It's a pity they were just a little short.

421
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:28,640
Since you've already seen signs of success,

422
00:24:28,640 --> 00:24:30,570
it means they are starting to grow.

423
00:24:30,760 --> 00:24:31,880
So it's fine.

424
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:34,200
You're not angry?

425
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:35,770
Why would I be angry?

426
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:38,660
Who would care for me if I got sick from anger?

427
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:40,520
Why did I go through so much trouble

428
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:42,920
to make them participate in this simulation task?

429
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:43,480
Because

430
00:24:43,760 --> 00:24:46,200
surprise tests show the real level best.

431
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:49,120
Even if they fail,

432
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:50,520
it's meaningful to them.

433
00:24:51,280 --> 00:24:52,810
Think about the beginning,

434
00:24:53,080 --> 00:24:54,410
how you made it through.

435
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:56,640
This is a necessary path.

436
00:24:58,000 --> 00:24:58,720
Mr. Qin,

437
00:24:58,960 --> 00:24:59,600
rest assured.

438
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:00,880
We will work hard.

439
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:02,130
I believe in you.

440
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:09,760
What exactly went wrong?

441
00:25:10,600 --> 00:25:12,460
The mission turned out like this.

442
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:15,240
I'll probably have to go back to the archives.

443
00:25:15,240 --> 00:25:16,840
I wanted to do something big,

444
00:25:17,160 --> 00:25:19,160
but I embarrassed myself this time.

445
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:21,730
This isn't our farewell dinner, is it?

446
00:25:23,240 --> 00:25:23,960
Boys,

447
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:26,000
cherish it and don't lose heart.

448
00:25:29,360 --> 00:25:30,760
The senior is quite nice,

449
00:25:30,840 --> 00:25:33,100
treating us to snacks at a time like this.

450
00:25:35,520 --> 00:25:36,080
This.

451
00:25:38,360 --> 00:25:39,290
You're all here.

452
00:25:39,760 --> 00:25:40,240
Come.

453
00:25:40,760 --> 00:25:42,890
I bought this for you at my own expense.

454
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:45,200
Eat more. Eat enough this time.

455
00:25:45,400 --> 00:25:46,600
Don't eat it anymore.

456
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:49,000
Why are you spacing out? You're not even eating.

457
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:50,860
Don't be discouraged. Keep it up.

458
00:25:51,280 --> 00:25:51,940
Veggie bun.

459
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:53,330
Hurry up and eat.

460
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:57,860
You're as mad as a little toad.

461
00:25:58,400 --> 00:25:59,120
It's fine.

462
00:25:59,960 --> 00:26:01,360
You should also say less.

463
00:26:01,920 --> 00:26:03,050
What does this mean?

464
00:26:04,040 --> 00:26:04,770
Brother Wei.

465
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:07,540
Guilinggao means returning to zero.

466
00:26:07,800 --> 00:26:09,400
They're saying our mission failed.

467
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:11,060
They want us to learn a lesson.

468
00:26:26,360 --> 00:26:27,640
Didn't Lao Qin tell us

469
00:26:28,560 --> 00:26:30,160
to always remember this day?

470
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:08,400
Weiwei.

471
00:27:09,240 --> 00:27:10,320
Come out and eat.

472
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:12,960
Did you hear me, Weiwei?

473
00:27:12,960 --> 00:27:14,240
Grandpa is calling you to eat.

474
00:27:14,240 --> 00:27:15,100
Say something.

475
00:27:33,360 --> 00:27:35,890
My parameters were just not accurate enough.

476
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:38,240
If you think they are wrong, you can tell me.

477
00:27:38,240 --> 00:27:39,280
And how did you know

478
00:27:39,280 --> 00:27:40,520
that was my final plan?

479
00:27:40,520 --> 00:27:41,980
Just not accurate enough?

480
00:27:42,880 --> 00:27:43,440
Wu Wei.

481
00:27:43,720 --> 00:27:44,980
You work in aerospace.

482
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:46,600
In our industry,

483
00:27:46,760 --> 00:27:48,220
there is no room for error.

484
00:27:48,240 --> 00:27:50,160
Otherwise, it will be a catastrophic disaster.

485
00:27:50,160 --> 00:27:52,560
And you are telling me it's just not accurate enough.

486
00:27:52,560 --> 00:27:54,840
I am confident that this plan is foolproof.

487
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:56,560
And it better reflects our ideas.

488
00:27:56,560 --> 00:27:57,480
The purpose of the mission

489
00:27:57,480 --> 00:27:59,120
is to use the most reliable plan

490
00:27:59,120 --> 00:28:01,040
to ensure the simulated flight control is completed smoothly,

491
00:28:01,040 --> 00:28:02,160
not to show off.

492
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:03,680
Don't impose your personal goals

493
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:05,080
onto the team's mission.

494
00:28:05,720 --> 00:28:06,720
Just having ideas

495
00:28:07,080 --> 00:28:07,840
won't work.

496
00:28:08,440 --> 00:28:09,480
What do you mean by that?

497
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:10,880
Choosing a better plan

498
00:28:11,280 --> 00:28:13,000
and trying to prove my abilities and ideas...

499
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:13,880
Is that wrong?

500
00:28:14,320 --> 00:28:16,120
You don't need to prove yourself.

501
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:17,000
You don't need to prove yourself,

502
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:18,360
not because you're so strong,

503
00:28:18,360 --> 00:28:20,160
but because you just don't care.

504
00:28:23,400 --> 00:28:25,800
Why did you come back without saying a word?

505
00:28:27,120 --> 00:28:27,920
I mean,

506
00:28:28,400 --> 00:28:30,560
did you mess up at work?

507
00:28:32,040 --> 00:28:33,300
Hey, watch your mouth.

508
00:28:33,840 --> 00:28:34,840
Watch your mouth.

509
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:38,040
What happened?

510
00:28:38,520 --> 00:28:39,320
Tell Grandpa.

511
00:28:43,800 --> 00:28:47,360
The simulation flight control we were in charge of failed.

512
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:49,880
I haven't even had time to share the good news.

513
00:28:49,880 --> 00:28:51,340
I got into flight control,

514
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:53,930
and now I might have to go back to the archives.

515
00:28:54,800 --> 00:28:56,260
I thought it was a big deal.

516
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:59,000
When your mom first did logistics at Aerospace City,

517
00:28:59,000 --> 00:29:00,680
it wasn't smooth sailing either.

518
00:29:00,680 --> 00:29:01,360
But she was never

519
00:29:01,360 --> 00:29:03,200
as dejected as you.

520
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:05,130
She was always very motivated.

521
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:06,160
Dad.

522
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:07,690
What did I say back then?

523
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:09,600
Didn't I say he shouldn't go?

524
00:29:09,640 --> 00:29:11,720
Said it was for some ideal, right?

525
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:14,200
You wanted to take a shortcut to the top.

526
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,160
You didn't make the shortcut.

527
00:29:15,160 --> 00:29:17,040
You just crashed yourself.

528
00:29:20,040 --> 00:29:21,280
I really don't understand.

529
00:29:21,280 --> 00:29:24,920
What magic does this aerospace stuff have?

530
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:26,000
It makes your Wu family,

531
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:28,600
both young and old, follow each other blindly.

532
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:30,780
You never give up until it's too late.

533
00:29:31,120 --> 00:29:33,480
You won't give up until you hit a brick wall.

534
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:35,960
That's exactly the style of our Wu family.

535
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:38,720
Once you set your mind on something,

536
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:40,640
you'll never give up easily.

537
00:29:41,080 --> 00:29:42,560
If you do it, it's for a lifetime.

538
00:29:42,560 --> 00:29:44,090
Not a minute or second less.

539
00:29:45,520 --> 00:29:47,800
Seeing your stubbornness,

540
00:29:48,080 --> 00:29:49,880
you really are like your mother.

541
00:29:50,520 --> 00:29:51,320
You,

542
00:29:51,840 --> 00:29:54,400
have always loved to copy her since childhood,

543
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:56,000
even loving aerospace.

544
00:29:56,280 --> 00:29:58,120
If you ask me, if you hadn't done this,

545
00:29:58,120 --> 00:29:59,850
you wouldn't be suffering now.

546
00:29:59,880 --> 00:30:00,960
Are you done yet?

547
00:30:03,080 --> 00:30:03,840
Fine.

548
00:30:05,320 --> 00:30:07,240
I can't argue with you two.

549
00:30:08,040 --> 00:30:10,360
All right, stop pulling a long face.

550
00:30:11,080 --> 00:30:12,880
As a man,

551
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:15,040
everyone has difficulties and hurdles.

552
00:30:15,040 --> 00:30:16,370
Let bygones be bygones.

553
00:30:16,600 --> 00:30:17,840
It's no big deal.

554
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:20,680
Pick yourself up from where you fell.

555
00:30:21,640 --> 00:30:22,200
Think about it.

556
00:30:22,200 --> 00:30:24,520
Why were you named Wu Wei?

557
00:30:25,080 --> 00:30:26,280
To be fearless.

558
00:30:27,440 --> 00:30:28,040
Drink up.

559
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:29,120
Come on.

560
00:30:29,720 --> 00:30:31,000
Didn't you say I couldn't drink?

561
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:31,880
Just listen to him.

562
00:30:31,880 --> 00:30:32,610
Want a drink?

563
00:30:37,200 --> 00:30:37,760
Come on.

564
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:41,530
All right, stop overthinking.

565
00:30:41,720 --> 00:30:42,440
Exactly.

566
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:08,880
Mr. Qin.

567
00:31:10,560 --> 00:31:11,440
Just you?

568
00:31:18,440 --> 00:31:20,480
The flight simulation reset to zero.

569
00:31:20,480 --> 00:31:22,010
Do you have anything to say?

570
00:31:22,440 --> 00:31:23,500
I'm sorry, Mr. Qin.

571
00:31:23,680 --> 00:31:25,410
I didn't do a good job this time.

572
00:31:27,600 --> 00:31:30,400
Does this proposal reflect your true capability?

573
00:31:31,720 --> 00:31:33,840
I personally recruited you.

574
00:31:34,600 --> 00:31:36,840
But ever since you joined Space City,

575
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:38,840
you've been a huge disappointment.

576
00:31:39,600 --> 00:31:40,320
I brought you here

577
00:31:40,320 --> 00:31:42,080
because your abilities and experience

578
00:31:42,080 --> 00:31:43,280
are above theirs.

579
00:31:43,280 --> 00:31:45,210
I thought you could unite this team

580
00:31:45,520 --> 00:31:46,450
and take charge.

581
00:31:47,360 --> 00:31:48,490
I brought Wu Wei here

582
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:50,040
to stir things up.

583
00:31:50,040 --> 00:31:52,240
But you can't just be a slacker forever.

584
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:54,760
Why did you come to Flight Control?

585
00:31:54,760 --> 00:31:56,420
Why did you choose this major?

586
00:31:57,360 --> 00:31:58,640
Think about it carefully.

587
00:31:58,640 --> 00:31:59,200
I...

588
00:32:00,160 --> 00:32:00,800
If...

589
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:03,320
If you are already

590
00:32:03,320 --> 00:32:04,920
losing interest in this job,

591
00:32:04,960 --> 00:32:05,890
have no passion,

592
00:32:06,160 --> 00:32:08,160
and can't find a direction to strive for,

593
00:32:08,160 --> 00:32:10,240
you don't have to wait until the internship ends.

594
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:11,520
You can leave right now.

595
00:32:11,520 --> 00:32:13,720
Because you don't deserve to stay here.

596
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:44,280
Wu Wei.

597
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:49,880
Are you okay?

598
00:32:54,800 --> 00:32:56,720
The simulated flight control mission failed.

599
00:32:56,720 --> 00:32:57,980
Don't take it too hard.

600
00:32:58,360 --> 00:32:59,280
It's a team mission.

601
00:32:59,280 --> 00:33:01,610
Everyone is responsible for the failure.

602
00:33:05,520 --> 00:33:06,960
I bought Ying Ziqi a cup.

603
00:33:08,080 --> 00:33:10,040
Didn't his cup break last time?

604
00:33:10,040 --> 00:33:11,760
So I bought him a new one.

605
00:33:12,640 --> 00:33:14,200
Just give it to him yourself.

606
00:33:14,200 --> 00:33:16,130
Just do me a favor and give it to him.

607
00:33:16,360 --> 00:33:17,160
Please.

608
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:23,800
Let me just say one more thing.

609
00:33:23,800 --> 00:33:25,860
I think you misunderstood Ying Ziqi.

610
00:33:25,880 --> 00:33:27,320
The simulated flight control failed this time.

611
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:28,850
I think he's very upset too.

612
00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:31,480
You don't need to make excuses for him.

613
00:33:31,480 --> 00:33:33,210
I'm not making excuses for him.

614
00:33:33,360 --> 00:33:34,400
If he wasn't upset,

615
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:36,600
he wouldn't have secretly reviewed it.

616
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:38,680
I think

617
00:33:38,680 --> 00:33:41,210
he just doesn't want to show it in front of you.

618
00:33:42,560 --> 00:33:44,090
Besides, for this mission,

619
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:46,000
you've already done a great job.

620
00:33:48,240 --> 00:33:48,720
Come on.

621
00:34:27,880 --> 00:34:28,920
I can't hear you.

622
00:34:31,159 --> 00:34:32,020
This is for you.

623
00:34:32,880 --> 00:34:33,639
Take it.

624
00:34:36,120 --> 00:34:38,250
Don't go yet. Let me ask you something.

625
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:42,520
Am I really a wimp in your eyes?

626
00:34:46,040 --> 00:34:47,500
Did you just realize that?

627
00:34:48,040 --> 00:34:50,719
A wimp, a show-off,

628
00:34:51,600 --> 00:34:54,000
and trying to run before I can walk.

629
00:34:54,920 --> 00:34:56,600
You're right, Ying Ziqi.

630
00:34:57,360 --> 00:35:00,160
We should have used your plan.

631
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:04,620
You don't need to take it all on yourself.

632
00:35:04,680 --> 00:35:05,640
Wait a minute.

633
00:35:05,920 --> 00:35:07,520
Tell me the truth.

634
00:35:09,480 --> 00:35:11,200
Do you really think

635
00:35:12,160 --> 00:35:14,360
I don't deserve to be in Flight Control,

636
00:35:14,480 --> 00:35:16,600
or the Muxing Team?

637
00:35:24,560 --> 00:35:27,960
Actually, during that rocket competition when we were kids,

638
00:35:29,040 --> 00:35:31,160
I wasn't mad at you.

639
00:35:32,080 --> 00:35:34,000
I was mad at myself.

640
00:35:35,320 --> 00:35:36,960
If I had paid attention,

641
00:35:38,080 --> 00:35:40,680
I could have finished the competition myself.

642
00:35:41,200 --> 00:35:43,400
I might have even won the championship.

643
00:35:45,640 --> 00:35:46,520
I thought...

644
00:35:48,480 --> 00:35:49,840
I thought giving the championship to my mom

645
00:35:49,840 --> 00:35:51,200
would make her better.

646
00:35:57,760 --> 00:36:00,220
I was always getting into trouble back then.

647
00:36:00,720 --> 00:36:01,760
I wasn't like you.

648
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:04,660
You were first in everything,

649
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:06,120
a model student,

650
00:36:06,960 --> 00:36:08,200
the chosen one.

651
00:36:10,880 --> 00:36:12,680
I never cared about being first.

652
00:36:15,480 --> 00:36:16,600
But that one time,

653
00:36:17,840 --> 00:36:18,700
I wanted to win.

654
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:23,520
I wanted my mom to be proud of me for once.

655
00:36:28,040 --> 00:36:29,320
But when I wanted to win the most,

656
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:30,880
when I needed it the most,

657
00:36:32,760 --> 00:36:33,690
I couldn't do it.

658
00:36:44,240 --> 00:36:45,320
Do you remember when we were kids,

659
00:36:45,320 --> 00:36:47,250
the wishes we made on the mountain?

660
00:36:48,680 --> 00:36:50,400
None of them came true.

661
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:11,360
What did you wish for?

662
00:37:11,760 --> 00:37:14,680
You, me, and Xiaoba,

663
00:37:15,200 --> 00:37:17,000
will be good friends forever.

664
00:37:17,240 --> 00:37:18,800
It won't come true if you say it out loud.

665
00:37:18,800 --> 00:37:20,060
Then why did you ask me?

666
00:37:22,320 --> 00:37:22,920
My turn.

667
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:26,160
To be good friends forever.

668
00:37:26,600 --> 00:37:28,600
To win the rocket competition.

669
00:37:29,360 --> 00:37:31,040
For Mom to get better.

670
00:37:35,440 --> 00:37:37,000
Ying Ziqi,

671
00:37:37,200 --> 00:37:38,000
Xiaoba, and I

672
00:37:38,560 --> 00:37:41,960
will be good friends forever and ever.

673
00:37:50,560 --> 00:37:53,220
Actually, I really envied you when we were kids.

674
00:37:54,200 --> 00:37:55,860
Your mom always supported you

675
00:37:56,680 --> 00:37:58,280
and never micromanaged you.

676
00:38:00,600 --> 00:38:01,440
Yeah.

677
00:38:02,240 --> 00:38:04,040
She supported me in everything.

678
00:38:05,120 --> 00:38:06,000
Then again.

679
00:38:07,160 --> 00:38:08,200
If you hadn't tricked me

680
00:38:08,200 --> 00:38:10,280
into going to the Youth Palace when we were kids,

681
00:38:10,280 --> 00:38:12,880
I wouldn't have become interested in aerospace,

682
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:14,800
let alone majored in it.

683
00:38:16,200 --> 00:38:18,800
I owe all of this to you.

684
00:38:22,920 --> 00:38:25,250
If it weren't for the rocket competition,

685
00:38:25,360 --> 00:38:27,960
I wouldn't have fallen in love with aerospace.

686
00:38:29,960 --> 00:38:31,480
But what's wrong with you?

687
00:38:32,680 --> 00:38:34,840
I couldn't even get into this place,

688
00:38:35,240 --> 00:38:37,280
yet you don't seem to care at all.

689
00:38:39,240 --> 00:38:40,840
I just don't get it.

690
00:38:42,840 --> 00:38:44,800
What exactly do you want to do?

691
00:38:46,120 --> 00:38:47,440
I wish I knew.

692
00:38:49,800 --> 00:38:51,040
I feel sick.

693
00:38:51,800 --> 00:38:53,060
Is it wrong not to know?

694
00:38:53,240 --> 00:38:54,720
I mean I feel sick.

695
00:38:58,040 --> 00:38:59,570
Don't throw up on the floor.

696
00:38:59,840 --> 00:39:01,700
Come on, let's go to the bathroom.

697
00:39:02,880 --> 00:39:03,520
Slow down.

698
00:39:03,880 --> 00:39:04,740
Don't throw up.

699
00:39:16,360 --> 00:39:19,760
Actually, during that rocket competition when we were kids,

700
00:39:20,880 --> 00:39:22,120
I wasn't mad at you.

701
00:39:23,880 --> 00:39:25,160
I was mad at myself.

702
00:39:45,640 --> 00:39:47,760
Muxing Team is amazing.

703
00:39:48,160 --> 00:39:49,760
We are amazing.

704
00:40:48,320 --> 00:40:49,800
Here, drink some water.

705
00:40:56,680 --> 00:40:57,280
Wipe it.

706
00:40:59,840 --> 00:41:01,040
No, don't.

707
00:41:03,880 --> 00:41:04,640
Wrong way.

708
00:41:05,960 --> 00:41:06,600
This way.

709
00:41:08,520 --> 00:41:09,840
I feel so terrible.

710
00:41:09,840 --> 00:41:10,760
Where is this?

711
00:41:10,760 --> 00:41:11,800
I can't get up.

712
00:41:12,200 --> 00:41:12,760
This way.

713
00:41:17,600 --> 00:41:18,840
Bro.

714
00:41:19,560 --> 00:41:22,120
The future depends on us.

715
00:41:22,320 --> 00:41:23,120
Amazing.

716
00:41:23,760 --> 00:41:26,160
If the future depends on you, we're doomed.

717
00:41:32,520 --> 00:41:33,250
So annoying.

718
00:41:37,840 --> 00:41:41,200
The Flight Control Center can't do without me.

719
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:43,720
Can't do without me.

720
00:41:57,600 --> 00:41:59,060
Did you kick me yesterday?

721
00:41:59,680 --> 00:42:02,280
Taking the opportunity for revenge. Is it fun?

722
00:42:03,080 --> 00:42:03,640
Eat.

723
00:42:13,200 --> 00:42:14,330
What else did you do?

724
00:42:16,240 --> 00:42:17,200
You apologized to me.

725
00:42:17,200 --> 00:42:19,260
I apologized to you? What do I owe you?

726
00:42:19,840 --> 00:42:22,320
You said for the rocket competition when we were kids,

727
00:42:22,320 --> 00:42:23,980
you shouldn't have blamed me.

728
00:42:24,360 --> 00:42:25,760
That was ages ago.

729
00:42:27,280 --> 00:42:28,410
That was drunk talk.

730
00:42:28,520 --> 00:42:29,920
Don't take it seriously.

731
00:42:30,240 --> 00:42:31,770
I didn't take it seriously.

732
00:42:34,320 --> 00:42:35,320
Keep making it up.

733
00:42:35,720 --> 00:42:36,720
Where are you going?

734
00:42:36,720 --> 00:42:38,480
To work at the archives.

735
00:43:00,720 --> 00:43:05,240
The names of spacecrafts and related missions in this series are fictionalized.

